        <comment xml:lang="en">0.0002 ha/ha (1.57E-4 ha/kg Potato) market for application of plant protection product, by sprayer
 Application by of plant protection products (pesticides and, if used, growth regulator and/or desiccant, but excluding fumigant) for potato production in Colorado includes 4 aerial spray passes and 7 passes with ground sprayer (based on detailed enterprise budgets).  Application by of plant protection products (pesticides and, if used, growth regulator and/or desiccant, but excluding fumigant) for potato production in Colorado includes 4 aerial spray passes and 7 passes with ground sprayer (based on detailed enterprise budgets).  
Detailed guidance for Colorado potato production is not available. Operations are drawn a multi-state comparison (Patterson, 2015) and the budgets on which it is based, and from a Klamath basin budget (Wilson, et al., 2015). Field operations are as identified in crop- and rotation-specific enterprise crop budgets supplied by the regional agricultural extension office (state specific unless otherwise noted) and matched to equipment type in the budget or crop guidance, along with pest management documentation (Hills, et al., 2018, 2020; Hirnyck &amp; Downey, 2006) and summary of practices for commercial production in the US (Belyea, 2010).  (Patterson, Paul 2015, Belyea S. et al 2010, Wilson, Robert et al 2015).  As the operation applies only to a portion of the harvested area, the number of passes has been scaled by the % of harvested area to which it applies (e.g., manure spreading or insecticide) as indicated by USDA statistics (applications) or USDA reports (manure use) or as otherwise indicated in enterprise crop budgets.
Source(s): 
Plastina A and Johanns A (2021) Iowa Farm Custom Rate Survey, 2021 (2018, 2019, 2020). Cooperative Extension Service, Iowa State University of Science and Technology. https://www.extension.iastate.edu/agdm/crops/pdf/a3-10.pdf; Plastina, Johanns, Massman (2020) 2020 Iowa Farm Custom Rate Survey File A3-10. Cooperative Extension Service, Iowa State University of Science and Technology. https://iastate.app.box.com/embed/s/hbsel0lckc7vle74v4jkg7mf0ph3z39s/file/630724245464; Plastina, Johanns, Wynne (2019) 2019 Iowa Farm Custom Rate Survey File A3-10. Cooperative Extension Service, Iowa State University of Science and Technology. https://www.extension.iastate.edu/monroe/sites/www.extension.iastate.edu/files/monroe/2019%20Custom%20Rate%20Survey.pdf; Plastina, Johanns, Welter (2018) 2018 Iowa Farm Custom Rate Survey File A3-10. Cooperative Extension Service, Iowa State University of Science and Technology. https://www.extension.iastate.edu/hancock/sites/www.extension.iastate.edu/files/hancock/2018_CustomRateSurvey.pdf
