      <intermediateExchange id="2b3065d2-97df-5a3e-9f56-b11ffdb4d6e3" unitId="86bbe475-8a8f-44d8-914c-e398787e7121" amount="2.24391473570666E-05" intermediateExchangeId="25209673-91f6-58a7-8254-7d320d3b50c9" activityLinkId="5973b3db-66c5-526e-9ddf-9740715ddc5d">
        <name xml:lang="en">application of plant protection product, fumigation</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">ha</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">2.24E-5 ha/kg application of plant protection product, fumigation (1. pass(es) per year). 
The field is treated with fumigant pre-planting (either in the spring before planting or fall after harvest of prior crop) to control soil-borne fungal diseases and pests. This application is distinct from application of other plant protection products.  Detailed guidance for Colorado potato production is not available. Operations are drawn a multi-state comparison (Patterson, 2015) and the budgets on which it is based, and from a Klamath basin budget (Wilson, et al., 2015).
 Field operations are as identified in crop- and rotation-specific enterprise crop budgets supplied by the regional agricultural extension office (state specific unless otherwise noted) and matched to equipment type in the budget or crop guidance, along with pest management documentation (Hills, et al., 2018, 2020; Hirnyck &amp; Downey, 2006) and summary of practices for commercial production in the US (Belyea, 2010).Field operations are as identified in crop- and rotation-specific enterprise crop budgets supplied by the regional agricultural extension office (state specific unless otherwise noted) and matched to equipment type in the budget or crop guidance, along with pest management documentation (Hills, et al., 2018, 2020; Hirnyck &amp; Downey, 2006) and summary of practices for commercial production in the US (Belyea, 2010).  
