        <name xml:lang="en">potassium nitrate</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">5.14E-4 kg potassium nitrate/kg Potato 
Quantities of specific fertiliser are calculated based on US fertiliser market share and nutrient compositions from the International Fertilizer Association data to meet total nutrient demand N-P-K-S: 161.88--156.82--58.44--45.53 kg/ha  (USDA NASS data for 2010, 2014, 2016), over reported cropped area of specified crop (includes all rotation patterns):  quantity of N applied to treated acres times percent of planted potato acres treated (USDA NASS) times share of N supplied by compound in U.S. consumption mix (ecoinvent and International Fertilizer Association 2019) times mass compound per mass N in compound.
Sources: 
USDA NASS (2021c) POTATO - APPLICATIONS, MEASURED IN LB / ACRE / YEAR, AVG (fertilizer and pesticides, amount, number of applications) - 2000-2021. US Department of Agriculture (USDA) National Agricultural Statistics Service. https://quickstats.nass.usda.gov (direct query: https://quickstats.nass.usda.gov/results/910944A6-DEB0-3216-B6B4-F5BA47F1D217); Ecoinvent U.S. consumption mix for N fertilisers, from IFA data; IFA (2021) Nutrient content in percentage - IFA Fertilizer Converter. International Fertilizer Association. https://www.ifastat.org/converter/fertilizer-converter/accessed 2021-06-24</comment>
