      <intermediateExchange id="6fe98890-a0bf-5ddd-872f-cabdf81e7f9f" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7" amount="0.0704225352112676" intermediateExchangeId="1f69b3bf-b3b1-41b2-9441-7efbc55f58bb" activityLinkId="feca3615-9820-5c0d-9098-80c996f7698e">
        <name xml:lang="en">potato seed, for setting</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Treated seed. This value is taken from guidance (enterprise crop budget) for potato production in Colorado (Patterson, Paul 2015) and average spacing and seed potato size (Belyea S. et al 2010). The dataset assumes conventional seed potato as opposed to genetically modified varieties. While there are some varieties of modified potato authorized in the US, they have limited availability and minor uptake (USDA 2021). The uncertainty parameters are calculated from the uncertainty on the yield and the  guidance variation from guidance for all states. 
Sources:
Patterson, Paul (2015) 2014 Cost of Potato Production Study for Colorado, Idaho, Washington and Wisconsin. University of Idaho College of Agricultural and Life Sciences. 
Belyea S. et al (2010) Commercial Potato Production in North America. The Potato Association of America. 
USDA (2021) BE Potato crop summary. USDA. https://www.ams.usda.gov/sites/default/files/media/BEPotatoSummary.pdf</comment>
        <uncertainty>
          <normal meanValue="0.0704225352112676" variance="0.0" varianceWithPedigreeUncertainty="0.0"/>
          <pedigreeMatrix reliability="3" completeness="1" temporalCorrelation="4" geographicalCorrelation="1" furtherTechnologyCorrelation="2"/>
        </uncertainty>
