        <name xml:lang="en">tillage, disking</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">ha</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">4.49E-5 ha/kg tillage, disking (2. pass(es) per year). 
 Detailed guidance for Colorado potato production is not available. Operations are drawn a multi-state comparison (Patterson, 2015) and the budgets on which it is based, and from a Klamath basin budget (Wilson, et al., 2015). Field operations are as identified in crop- and rotation-specific enterprise crop budgets supplied by the regional agricultural extension office (state specific unless otherwise noted) and matched to equipment type in the budget or crop guidance, along with pest management documentation (Hills, et al., 2018, 2020; Hirnyck &amp; Downey, 2006) and summary of practices for commercial production in the US (Belyea, 2010).  Potato is a full tillage crop. 
Sources:
Patterson, Paul (2015) 2014 Cost of Potato Production Study for Colorado, Idaho, Washington and Wisconsin. University of Idaho College of Agricultural and Life Sciences. 
Wilson, Robert et al (2015) Sample Costs to Produce Potatoes. University of California Cooperative Extension. https://coststudyfiles.ucdavis.edu/uploads/cs_public/4e/f5/4ef54da3-114e-4952-a66a-049765b9a747/15potatofreshmktklamathfinaldraftdec10.pdf
