      <elementaryExchange id="027372e2-e0e5-5b3d-b5e8-ea538fc58a07" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7" casNumber="007664-41-7" amount="0.000309894396671333" elementaryExchangeId="0f440cc0-0f74-446d-99d6-8ff0e97a2444" formula="H3N">
        <name xml:lang="en">Ammonia</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Ammonia volatilised from applied mineral and organic fertilisers, 13.8 kg NH3/ha (3.1E-4kg NH3/kg Potato) total, 13.8 kg NH3/ha (3.1E-4 kg NH3/kg Potato) from synthetic fertilisers, 0.0 kg NH3/ha (0.E+0 kg NH3/kg Potato) from manure. NH3 from volatilisation of mineral fertilisers is calculated using Tier 2 emission factors (temperate climate, specific fertiliser) from the European Environment Agency, EMEP/EEA 3Da1, Table3.2 (EEA 2019). NH3 from manure application is calculated with emission factors provided in EMEP/EEA 3.D.a.2.a (Animal manure applied to soils) (EEA 2019) for manure types used as (fraction TAN in total N)*(EF manure spreading per TAN) for each animal group and type. (kg NH3-N/kg N applied: ). The emissions from manure calculated here do not account for the change in N mineralization and phosphate runoff with incorporation type or time. Where impacts from manure application are expected to be significant, this should be considered as N volatilisation during and after application of manure ranges from as low as 1% N with direct injection to ~5% with immediate incorporation to 20-40% without incorporation (Sawyer J, Mallarino A P (2016) Using Manure Nutrients for Crop Production. Cooperative Extension Service, Iowa State University of Science and Technology. https://store.extension.iastate.edu/product/12874and Midwast Plan Services MWPS-18, 3ed)..  NH3 from volatilisation of mineral fertilisers is calculated using Tier 2 emission factors (temperate climate, specific fertiliser) from the European Environment Agency, EMEP/EEA 3Da1, Table3.2 (EEA 2019). NH3 from manure application is calculated with emission factors provided in EMEP/EEA 3.D.a.2.a (Animal manure applied to soils) (EEA 2019) for manure types used as (fraction TAN in total N)*(EF manure spreading per TAN) for each animal group and type. (kg NH3-N/kg N applied: ). The emissions from manure calculated here do not account for the change in N mineralization and phosphate runoff with incorporation type or time. Where impacts from manure application are expected to be significant, this should be considered as N volatilisation during and after application of manure ranges from as low as 1% N with direct injection to ~5% with immediate incorporation to 20-40% without incorporation (Sawyer J, Mallarino A P (2016) Using Manure Nutrients for Crop Production. Cooperative Extension Service, Iowa State University of Science and Technology. https://store.extension.iastate.edu/product/12874and Midwast Plan Services MWPS-18, 3ed).</comment>
        <uncertainty>
          <lognormal meanValue="0.000309894396671333" mu="-8.07927897442041" variance="0.008" varianceWithPedigreeUncertainty="0.0172"/>
          <pedigreeMatrix reliability="2" completeness="3" temporalCorrelation="4" geographicalCorrelation="1" furtherTechnologyCorrelation="1"/>
        </uncertainty>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">azane</synonym>
