        <name xml:lang="en">Phosphate</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Phosphate leaching to ground water 0.14 kg PO4/ha (3.141E-6 kg/kg Potato): 7.E-2 kg PO4/ha from manure and 7.E-2 kg PO4/ha from leaching from arable land.  Phosphate leaching to ground water is calculated using the SALCA-P model (Prasuhn 2006) with an average leaching factor for arable lands and the amount of phosphate in any applied manure, as implemented in the ecoinvent agricultural LCI tool (see Ecoinvent_Too_Model_Description_20191015.pdf). Does not incorporate state or county data on soils, slope or conservation drainage infrastructure. Calculated with the ecoinvent agricultural LCI tool.</comment>
